<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=2186&amp;p=18397#p18397"><![CDATA[
so you mean instead of <br /><br />11111111 11111111 00000000 00000000 00000000 00000000 11111111 11111111 etc, <br /><br />11111111 01010101 01010101 00000000 00000000 01010101 01010101 11111111 etc.<br /><br />which would be the same as <br /><br />FF FF 00 00 00 00 FF FF<br />to<br />FF 55 55 00 00 55 55 FF (55 and AA are interchangeable as far as i care, too lazy to look up which 01010101 actually is).<br /><br />this would create a lower frequency wave that has lower volume/amplitude, but it would also create some nice aliasing that would make it not sound quite like a triangle anymore (or like two triangles, one at a low octave, one at many octaves higher).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=34">RushJet1</a> — Thu Oct 12, 2006 2:59 pm</p><hr />
