<div class="quotetitle">blargg wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Delta Modulation Channel or Delta Pulse Code Modulation Channel. Samples played are limited to those whose deltas are generally always +2 or -2, always stair-stepping up or down.<br /></div><br /><br />and this is why triangle waves were generally a good idea since that is how they are made (well basically anyway).  the only thing i don't like about this is how lower frequencies are higher in volume (depending on how the lower frequency is reached, but below a certain point it's inevitable that lower freqs are louder and higher are softer... can't get around that without aliasing, so i've just got to accept it!)<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=34">RushJet1</a> — Wed Oct 11, 2006 3:52 pm</p><hr />
